'''Zena Denise Clarke Tessensohn''' (16 December 1909 – 25 July 1991) was a Singaporean sports official. She was one of the [[Girls' Sports Club]]'s founders.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=[[The Straits Times]] |url=http://newspapers.nl.sg/Digitised/Article/straitstimes19910726.2.53.6.aspx |date=July 26, 1991 |title=Leading woman official, 81, dies |page=38 |accessdate=February 3, 2013 }}</ref> In 2018 she was inducted into the [[Singapore Women's Hall of Fame]].<ref name="swhof">{{cite web |title=Zena Clarke Tessensohn |url=https://www.swhf.sg/profiles/zena-clarke-tessensohn/ |website=The Honored Inductees to the Singapore Women's Hall of Fame |publisher=Singapore Council of Women's Organisations |accessdate=8 November 2018}}</ref>

